items.badge_description: Canning is all the rage and it's not hard to see why - travels well, more environmentally friendly, and no need to carry your bottle opener. That's 350 checkins with the serving style of Can. Try 5 more for Level 71! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast
We believe in IPA and you should too. You certainly have a taste for the hops! That's 35 different IPAs. Try 5 more for Level 8! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

user.bio: Inner West brewery enthusiast and bon vivant. Currently favouring boozy grapefruity IIPAs.

items.checkin_comment: P&P S7E4: Classic east-coast hazy, NZ hop diesel notes come through clearly. Just a touch rich for our tastes, but still a top-notch NEIPA.

user.bio: Covers the beers reviewed on Pixels & Pints podcast, Aussie larakins discussing pop culture & beer. Check us on itunes!

items.badge_description: Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 435 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%.  Try 5 more for Level 88!

You may not be able to see through the haze, but that juicy, hoppy goodness goes down smooth. What started as a trend is here to stay. That's 140 different beers with the style of IPA - New England / Hazy, Pale Ale - New England / Hazy, IPA - Milkshake, or Pale Ale - Milkshake. Try 5 more for Level 29!

items.checkin_comment: Citrus, white grape and mild tropical nose. Nasty herbal Kiwi hop flavours upfront. Delicious Nelson flavours kick in and dominate. Yellow flesh stonefruit notes with hints of citrus peel. This is a bit of a Jekyll and Hyde brew for me.

user.bio: Crawley born. Norfolk emigre. If it’s beer it’ll most likely get a score over 4.
Some people are like clouds….When they disappear it’s a beautiful day.
"Travel is fatal to prejudice, bigotry, and narrow-mindedness..." (Samuel Clemens).
Straddling the line of NPC and main character

Keeping my friends close,

South Aussie livin’ in Melbourne... Go Port Adelaide!
Coffee black, whiskey neat, and beer like my women: stout and bitter
Work less, play more, drink better beer

items.badge_description: All aboard the brew express! Grab a pint and enjoy the ride! That's a beer at 5 different places categorized as a Train or Train Station. Check out 5 more places for Level 80!
